commit_message:
pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

This patch fix this problem.

Change-Id: If0bc42891a0714cc9b37b9c211388db20555ea7e
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/nova refs/changes/69/189569/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: passenv = http_proxy HTTP_PROXY https_proxy HTTPS_PROXY

commit_message:
Fix the broken gate about qos

Neutron used to notify deleting qos and then actually delete qos.
Now, it changes to delete qos first and then notify deleting qos.

[1] 8fcba9dec801a0fb57ff29f97838958f083c8131

This patch changes the code to get qos from nb db.

Change-Id: I310793127762bb76591fa8fc678ac5e8b53353e7
Closes-bug: #1650149

commit_message:
Replace logging with oslo_log.

The oslo.log (logging) configuration library provides standardized
configuration for all openstack projects. It also provides custom
formatters, handlers and support for context specific logging (like
resource id's etc).

Change-Id: I3117a6c9b5283005ee604f569bc4549acc2d3160

commit_message:
Privileged cleanup

Comparing privileged settings before and after helming has shown
some regressions. This PS removes privilege from containers that
didn't have it before.

Change-Id: I5dc70c1c8b8bc7b491970d14cd7d77c3d2678b67

commit_message:
Introduce roles into the feature matrix

test-matrix.py has a new cli option, for which role the node will play.
If it is a subnode, the starting set of services will be emitted,
that matches the current logic.

Logic regarding flags like DEVSTACK_GATE_NEUTRON,
DEVSTACK_GATE_NEUTRON_DVR, DEVSTACK_GATE_IRONIC is now moved to the
feature matrix.

Co-Authored-By: Julia Varlamova <jvarlamova@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Michal Dulko <michal.dulko@intel.com>

Change-Id: Ief1b74cbc01235d9f52d08add930781f3a0ae71b

Add support for nic and az in cluster grow

Added support for the nic and az parameter in cluster grow for
mongodb.

Redis and cassandra already fully supported these fields.

Closes-Bug: #1641675

commit_message:
Enhance the parameter check for "path"

1\Enhances the parameter check for "path" in cluster
collect. After that, senlin client will behave identically with
openstack client when no path is given.
2\ Adds related unit test.

Change-Id: I907e739a7ee63d6a37f0c1ec69e37df1ab8b24df

commit_message:
Tweak trove devstack plugin

Tweak the trove devstack plugin to force KVM if possible. This change
is semi-experimental. I would like to see how it performs in the gate,
it seems to be fine on my local machine. It takes some precautions to
only force kvm if it is possible.

In speaking with infra, there are also some known stability issues
with kvm and part of the experiment here is to see what those are. The
other part is to quantify the improvement that it brings to the trove
gate.

Change-Id: I209d3202b4f6414cd3430c11f2ccdb8d5b541d94
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/trove refs/changes/11/412011/4 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: # Update nova configuration if [[ "$(cat /sys/module/kvm_*/parameters/nested)" == "Y" ]]; then echo_summary "Configuring Nova to use KVM." NOVA_CONF_DIR=${NOVA_CONF_DIR:-/etc/nova} NOVA_CONF=${NOVA_CONF:-${NOVA_CONF_DIR}/nova.conf} iniset $NOVA_CONF libvirt cpu_mode "host-passthrough" iniset $NOVA_CONF libvirt virt_type "kvm" else echo_summary "*** Unable to configure Nova to use KVM, your mileage may vary." fi

commit_message:
Make nova-manage emit a traceback when things blow up

If we hit an unhandled error in nova-manage we don't
get a traceback currently which makes debugging the actual
failure hard. This change emits a traceback in main() when
we get an unhandled exception up from one of the subcommands.

Change-Id: Id8b8ad3c97c6834abc4290319cd6f2cd5aafa479
Related-Bug: #1650694
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/nova refs/changes/24/412024/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: import traceback except Exception: print(_("An error has occurred:\n%s") % traceback.format_exc())
deleted_lines: except Exception as ex: print(_("error: %s") % ex)

commit_message:
XenAPI: Remove ovs_integration_bridge default value

xapi1 as the default ovs_integration_bridge can be incorrect as it is
dependent on the environment. xapi<n> are internal bridges that are
incrementally defined from zero. Operators should set this config value
to the integration bridge used between all guests and the compute host
in their environment.

UpgradeImpact
Change-Id: If463936553cc663fd0bd018ccc9b8395bbdff6d9

subject: Use hostname -s instead of hostnamectl --transient
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-12-14 20:51:44.000000000', 'files': ['deployed-server/deployed-server.yaml'], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/commit/4e8d5aa2c3bc7e811d2592856549faf809143971', 'message': 'Use hostname -s instead of hostnamectl --transient

This patch updates the deployed-server interface to use a
simple hostname -s. The previous hostnamectl --transient
can pick up extra domain name configuration in some cases
that can cause very odd hostname generation if used
with the tripleo-heat-template host file generation.

This would actually break the new undercloud t-h-t installer
in that some of the /etc/hosts entries would be invalid
(no IP address) due to substring replacements failing in
a variety of odd hostname situations. Simplifying the
hostname of deployed servers to just the short version seems
the most sensable way to avoid all this.

Change-Id: Ia7e636d021f948ea5234475cef02f666d8ce6999
'}]
commit_message:
Use hostname -s instead of hostnamectl --transient

This patch updates the deployed-server interface to use a
simple hostname -s. The previous hostnamectl --transient
can pick up extra domain name configuration in some cases
that can cause very odd hostname generation if used
with the tripleo-heat-template host file generation.

This would actually break the new undercloud t-h-t installer
in that some of the /etc/hosts entries would be invalid
(no IP address) due to substring replacements failing in
a variety of odd hostname situations. Simplifying the
hostname of deployed servers to just the short version seems
the most sensable way to avoid all this.

Change-Id: Ia7e636d021f948ea5234475cef02f666d8ce6999
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates refs/changes/52/410952/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: host=$(hostname -s)

Update upper-constaints for virtualenv

Current 14.0.6 has an issue[*] which leds to failures in gates
(for example [1])

[1] http://logs.openstack.org/06/350106/14/check/gate-novaclient-dsvm-functional-mitaka-ubuntu-trusty-nv/7ce219e/

commit_message:
bump minimum keystonemiddleware to 4.12.0

This is part of a larger effort to solve the issue of long running
operations timing out when a token expires. The change to allow
an expired token to be validated was introduced in 4.12.0. The
server side code has already been implemented in ocata-2.

see bp allow-expires

Change-Id: I2e23c6bb7d51ee1486693bb40d3c6a3a8b2cce4f

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-11-16 16:34:55.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/nova/commit/bbdeb2ac24cd5999cb3e6e069a1a847850c7aa12', 'message': "rt: pass nodename to internal methods

We would like to remove the resource tracker's nodename attribute and
have the resource tracker treat Ironic baremetal resource nodes like any
other consumable resource in the system. This means having the Ironic
virt driver register Ironic baremetal nodes as resource providers in the
new placement API and creating an inventory record of a quantity of 1
with a resource class of the Ironic node.resource_class attribute. The
problem we have is that currently the nova-compute daemon keeps a
ResourceTracker object in memory for each Ironic compute node in the
entire deployment (or a segment of Ironic nodes if using Newton and the
Ironic hashring functionality). We would like to have a single resource
tracker object that manages a set of resource providers instead of
having a resource tracker for each Ironic baremetal node.

This patch performs some initial surgery on the resource tracker to pass
a nodename parameter to a number of methods.  The first one up is the
simple internal methods:

- _set_instance_host_and_nodename()
- _create_migration()
- _claim_existing_migraton()
- _move_claim()

Once the internal methods are cleaned, we will modify the public methods
called by the nova.compute.manager.Manager object to pass a nodename
parameter and remove the resource tracker's internal nodename attribute.
This will allow us to only have a single ResourceTracker object instance
(and thus a single scheduler reporting client object) on the
nova-compute daemon. The net result of this should be easier to reason
about resource tracking, more consistency in how resources are accounted
for, and a smaller memory-footprint for nova-compute when running Ironic
deployments.

Change-Id: I1b99fa48cc7902887a939d25097704eab6bb9c7a

commit_message:
rt: pass nodename to internal methods

We would like to remove the resource tracker's nodename attribute and
have the resource tracker treat Ironic baremetal resource nodes like any
other consumable resource in the system. This means having the Ironic
virt driver register Ironic baremetal nodes as resource providers in the
new placement API and creating an inventory record of a quantity of 1
with a resource class of the Ironic node.resource_class attribute. The
problem we have is that currently the nova-compute daemon keeps a
ResourceTracker object in memory for each Ironic compute node in the
entire deployment (or a segment of Ironic nodes if using Newton and the
Ironic hashring functionality). We would like to have a single resource
tracker object that manages a set of resource providers instead of
having a resource tracker for each Ironic baremetal node.

This patch performs some initial surgery on the resource tracker to pass
a nodename parameter to a number of methods.  The first one up is the
simple internal methods:

- _set_instance_host_and_nodename()
- _create_migration()
- _claim_existing_migraton()
- _move_claim()

Once the internal methods are cleaned, we will modify the public methods
called by the nova.compute.manager.Manager object to pass a nodename
parameter and remove the resource tracker's internal nodename attribute.
This will allow us to only have a single ResourceTracker object instance
(and thus a single scheduler reporting client object) on the
nova-compute daemon. The net result of this should be easier to reason
about resource tracking, more consistency in how resources are accounted
for, and a smaller memory-footprint for nova-compute when running Ironic
deployments.

Change-Id: I1b99fa48cc7902887a939d25097704eab6bb9c7a
blueprint: custom-resource-classes

commit_message:
Remove all code related to HTTPClient

In previous patch we switched to use SessionClient in all cases. It means that all
HTTPClient code is redundant now.

"}, {'number': 9, 'created': '2016-06-17 12:22:16.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/python-novaclient/commit/96f89d8aa7f839014007f83db7e9ff8d339113ae', 'message': 'Create Session instance if possible

We should not care about autentication, so it would be nice to move from
HTTPClient to Session implementation. Currently, there is several cases
which are not covered by Session, so we cannot delete HTTPClient at all,
but let's use Session object in all other cases.

Related changes:
 - cert argument is now transmitted to novaclient.v2.Client and to
   novaclient.client._construct_http_client;
 - "extensions" and "no_cache" arguments of _construct_http_client are
   removed. Since they were not used and _construct_http_client is a
   private method, we can do it silently and without dreprecation.

Change-Id: Ibb99fdafbf02b3e92f1a5d04d168151b3400b901
'}, {'number': 10, 'created': '2016-06-21 10:12:29.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/python-novaclient/commit/063dae781547590555849b64770dabd618880270', 'message': 'Create keystone session instance if possible

We should not care about autentication, so it would be nice to move from
novaclient.client.HTTPClient to novaclient.client.Session implementation.
Currently, there are several cases which are not covered by Session, so we
cannot delete HTTPClient at all, but let's use Session object in all other
cases.
Also it will help to support keystone V3.

Changes in this patch:
 - create token auth if token is specified;
 - create password auth if username and password is specified;
 - extend novaclient.client.Client, novaclient.v2.Client and
   novaclient.client._construct_http_client with new arguments(all of them
   are already exist in CLI):
    * cert;
    * project_domain_id;
    * project_domain_name;
    * user_domain_id;
    * user_domain_name.
 - rename arguments:
    * interface -> endpoint_type . We used both of these arguments in
      different places. let's unify an interface of novaclient.client.Client
      and use only endpoint_type.
    * bypass_url -> endpoint_override . It would be nice to have the similar
      arguments as other OpenStack clients had.
 - remove "extensions" and "no_cache" arguments of _construct_http_client.
   They were not used and since _construct_http_client is a private method, we
   can do it silently without deprecation.

Change-Id: Ibb99fdafbf02b3e92f1a5d04d168151b3400b901

commit_message:
Create keystone session instance if not present

Since all authentication plugins should be stored in Keystone, there is no
need to share responsibility for authentication stuff with Keystone team.
Let's use convinient and the right way to use keystone - keystone sessions.
We have own adapter for it - novaclient.client.Session which can be used in
100% cases of novaclient usage. Let's create session object if it is not
transmitted via arguments and get rid of novaclient.client.HTTPClient
implementation.

NOTE: novaclient.client.HTTPClient and all related code will be removed
      separately.

Co-Authored-By: Clenimar Filemon <clenimar@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
Change-Id: Ibb99fdafbf02b3e92f1a5d04d168151b3400b901

added_lines: from keystoneauth1 import loading from keystoneauth1 import session as ksession self._adapters[url] = ksession.TCPKeepAliveAdapter() # FIXME(andreykurilin): reduce number of parameters restricted for session # initialization. if not any((session, bypass_url, os_cache, proxy_tenant_id, proxy_token, http_log_debug, connection_pool, auth_plugin, auth_token)): loader = loading.get_plugin_loader("password") if not auth: auth = loader.load_from_options(username=username, user_id=user_id, password=password, project_id=project_id, tenant_id=tenant_id, auth_url=auth_url) session = ksession.Session(auth=auth, verify=(not insecure), timeout=timeout, cert=cacert, user_agent=user_agent)

commit_message:
Make SessionClient interface similar to HTTPClient

HttpClient will be deprecated soon and SessionClient will be used by default.
To not break integration novaclient with other project at the step of moving
from HTTPClient, SessionClient should have similar interface.

Change-Id: I855ccc5160dc7628f4550e93bf133adf8263aace

Deprecate connection_pool variable

This is the last variable which is redundant in case of SessionClient.
After this patch we will be able to use SessionClient in 100% usecases.

Transmit all auth related vars from cli to inner methods

user_domain_name arguments to constract SessionClient in proper way.

These variables will be used in further patches

commit_message:
Add version pin for image list function

image functions deprecated after v2.35 but we didn't pin the
version for them, so when use 2.37 by default won't work.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/392523/ fixed others but
unfortunately list function is missing

test_readonly_nova.py was removed as it's only for 2.35 check
while through this patch, >2.35 can be used

Change-Id: Ia1157dcb68971c5f64f7ab068fc647f25cd265e4
Related-Bug: 1638506
Closes-Bug: 1650617

commit_message:
Modify mistake of scsi adapter type class

The value of scsi adapter type class from key
'VirtualBusLogicController' was mistaken as 'paraVirtual",
which is supposed to be 'busLogic'. This patch is to fix it.

TrivalFix

Change-Id: I96c66c342ba82bf831cf15db762034b21ca7f7eb

commit_message:
Limit Kombu to <4

oslo.messaging is not compatible with Kombu 4 and superior. There's no
point in excluding each micro version of 4.0, which breaks e.g.
Ceilometer gate for several days each time Kombu decide to do a bug fix
release.

oslo.messaging needs to release with a correct indication of what it
supports, and it cannot do it currently because of the content of this
repository.

Change-Id: Ieec53c3ac1d3d9ae69f58f378381d3d94a8ce3ac

commit_message:
Fix ovs test for xenial

The change Ie3ee722b9fe6b5b1798fa52bd68ae3b656a8bdf8 switched the
default Ubuntu version that we test from trusty to xenial. Unfortunately
the vswitch::ovs tests assumed trusty for the platform params and were
not properly checking against trusty vs xenial. This change updates the
default platform params for Ubuntu to reflect the differences.

Change-Id: I88333bb571a924ad192aca86aa032c86a509a989

added_lines: List of efforts the Nova development team is prioritizing for reviews in the Ocata release (in no particular order). +-------------------------------------------+-----------------------+ | Priority | Primary Contacts | +===========================================+=======================+ | `Cells V2`_ | `Dan Smith`_ | +-------------------------------------------+-----------------------+ | `Resource Providers`_ | `Jay Pipes`_ | +-------------------------------------------+-----------------------+ | `API Improvements`_ | `Alex Xu`_ | +-------------------------------------------+-----------------------+ | `Network Aware Scheduling`_ | `John Garbutt`_ | +-------------------------------------------+-----------------------+ .. _Dan Smith: https://launchpad.net/~danms .. _Jay Pipes: https://launchpad.net/~jaypipes .. _Alex Xu: https://launchpad.net/~xuhj .. _John Garbutt: https://launchpad.net/~johngarbutt Cells v2 -------- A single cells v2 deployment was made possible in the Newton release, and CI testing was added, but cells v2 was still optional as of Newton. In Ocata, the goal is to support multiple cells v2 cells in a deployment. There are several priority efforts to get us there. * `Scheduler interaction for cells v2`_: This moves instance creation to the nova-conductor service so that when the scheduler picks a host, the instance is built in a specific cell. There are no plans in Ocata to support rebuilds or other instance move operations, i.e. migrations, between cells. * `Quotas in the API cell`_: The quotas tables have moved to the API database but we want to avoid an 'up-call' from the compute cells to the API when handling quota commits and rollbacks. With cells v2 we have an opportunity to rethink how Nova supports counting resources and tracking quota, so this effort aims to move quota handling to a more simplified solution which is more eventually consistent and avoids invalid over-quota failures by design. * Support a simple python merge operation when sorting and/or filtering a list of instances across multiple cells. Long-term this should be handled by `Searchlight`_ but for Ocata we will have a simple but albeit less performant solution. * Continuous integration testing with cells v2 enabled by default. We aim to make cells v2 required in Ocata deployments, and to get there we need to have the community CI jobs running with cells v2. This will require changes to grenade for upgrade testing and also testing multiple cells v2 cells with the multinode job. .. _Scheduler interaction for cells v2: ../specs/ocata/approved/cells-scheduling-interaction.html .. _Quotas in the API cell: ../specs/ocata/approved/cells-count-resources-to-check-quota-in-api.html .. _Searchlight: http://docs.openstack.org/developer/searchlight/ Resource Providers ------------------ `scheduler interaction <../specs/ocata/approved/resource-providers-scheduler-db-filters.html>`_ `resource classes <../specs/ocata/approved/custom-resource-classes.html>`_ API Improvements ---------------- These are required for cells v2. Maybe lump this in above. `query param validation <../specs/ocata/approved/consistent-query-parameters-validation.html>`_ `limit instance sort/filter params <https://review.openstack.org/#/c/393205/>`_ Network Aware Scheduling ------------------------ This is required for cells v2. Maybe lump this in above. `network aware scheduling <../specs/ocata/approved/prep-for-network-aware-scheduling-ocata.html>`_

commit_message:
Add ZaqarApiNetwork to the service net map

Without this Zaqar API will fail to run due to a missing bind
IP address in the config file.

Change-Id: Icd0a6e85b7455e89f37f05399146d5e743359da8
Closes-bug: #1650307

commit_message:
Some more dep container features

Add support for dynamic enable/disable, overriding vars explicitly
and supporting dynamic env vars from Values.

See the # License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations # under the License. import mock from oslo_utils import uuidutils import six import testtools from senlin.common import exception as exc from senlin.objects import event as eo class TestEvent(testtools.TestCase): def setUp(self): super(TestEvent, self).setUp() self.ctx = mock.Mock() @mock.patch.object(eo.Event, 'get') def test_find_by_uuid(self, mock_get): x_event = mock.Mock() mock_get.return_value = x_event aid = uuidutils.generate_uuid() result = eo.Event.find(self.ctx, aid) self.assertEqual(x_event, result) mock_get.assert_called_once_with(self.ctx, aid) @mock.patch.object(eo.Event, 'get_by_short_id') @mock.patch.object(eo.Event, 'get') def test_find_by_short_id(self, mock_get, mock_shortid): mock_get.return_value = None x_event = mock.Mock() mock_shortid.return_value = x_event aid = uuidutils.generate_uuid() result = eo.Event.find(self.ctx, aid, project_safe=False) self.assertEqual(x_event, result) mock_get.assert_called_once_with(self.ctx, aid, project_safe=False) mock_shortid.assert_called_once_with(self.ctx, aid, project_safe=False) @mock.patch.object(eo.Event, 'get_by_short_id') def test_find_by_short_id_directly(self, mock_shortid): x_event = mock.Mock() mock_shortid.return_value = x_event aid = 'abcdef' result = eo.Event.find(self.ctx, aid, project_safe=True) self.assertEqual(x_event, result) mock_shortid.assert_called_once_with(self.ctx, aid, project_safe=True) @mock.patch.object(eo.Event, 'get_by_short_id') def test_find_not_found(self, mock_shortid): mock_shortid.return_value = None ex = self.assertRaises(exc.ResourceNotFound, eo.Event.find, self.ctx, 'BOGUS') self.assertEqual("The event (BOGUS) could not be found.", six.text_type(ex)) mock_shortid.assert_called_once_with(self.ctx, 'BOGUS')

added_lines: from neutron_lib.plugins import directory # Override the create method here to ensure that the VIP port # associated with this load balancer has its 'admin_state_up' field # set to True. If it is set to False, midonet will not pass traffic # through the VIP. def create(self, context, obj, **kwargs): plugin = directory.get_plugin() port = plugin.get_port(context, obj.vip_port_id) if not port.get('admin_state_up'): port['admin_state_up'] = True plugin.update_port(context, port['id'], {'port': port}) return super(MidonetLoadBalancerManager, self).create( context, obj, **kwargs)

commit_message:
[kolla] openstack tag 3.0.0 is not available

when executing "kolla-ansible deploy", kolla always try to find 3.0.0 tags.
But now 3.0.0 tag of openstack is not available at https://hub.docker.
And 3.0.1 is available now

Change-Id: I2a706dc03361bba127878eb873ae15aa5d413dc6
Closes-Bug: #1640716

commit_message:
Add customization for wsgi process display name

when ceilometer api is deployed in httpd, however
 the process name is like '/usr/sbin/httpd -DFOREGROUND',
it is ambiguous and make monitoring more difficult.
the aodh, gnocchi module are also like that.
so we should set an appropriate name for wsgi process.

Change-Id: I5e8c9be062a88e9ed6442e6cbce6573fba385030
Related-Bug: #1626550

commit_message:
Revert "add mysql minimum version check"

This reverts commit 57bbee6e54d2cc90e11041d7bb1dc6543fbf7c5a.

This patch fails with MariaDB, and other MySQL variants, as the version
numbering is not consistent.

Change-Id: I789eeb026c69d6e150403cd4e248eace34f443d0
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/gnocchi refs/changes/63/411763/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
deleted_lines: def _is_rdbms_compatible(connection): dialect = connection.dialect.dialect_description version = connection.dialect.server_version_info return not (dialect.startswith('mysql') and version < (5, 6, 4)) @staticmethod with self.facade.reader_connection() as connection: if not self._is_rdbms_compatible(connection): raise RuntimeError("MySQL minimum required version is " "5.6.4")

commit_message:
Fix Gate: Force pip2 instead of pip

Something appears to have caused the xenial guests to install all
python libraries into python 3.5 directories and therefore the guest
won't launch. This change forces pip2 and in theory should get around
that.

Moved Redis and PostgreSQL installs after the trove-dep ones.

Change-Id: I3bbe3bafa7ea3e627272103ac16a38f6a32a8a06
Partial-Bug: #1650382

commit_message:
Add vagrant file for setting devstack for Zun

This patch adds necessary files and script for setting up
a zun devstack environment through vagrant. This will help
to boost productivity of zun developers.

Implements: blueprint vagrant-support-zun
Change-Id: Iacbf777b46208d7b1d52390b9c4a3c5a4229573e
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/zun refs/changes/54/411354/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: #!/bin/sh export OS_USER=vagrant BASHPATH=$(dirname "$0"\") echo "run script from $BASHPATH" # update system export DEBIAN_FRONTEND noninteractive sudo apt-get update sudo apt-get install -qqy git # determine checkout folder PWD=$(su "$OS_USER" -c "cd && pwd") DEVSTACK=$PWD/devstack # check if devstack is already there if [ ! -d "$DEVSTACK" ] then echo "Download devstack into $DEVSTACK" # clone devstack su "$OS_USER" -c "cd && git clone -b master https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack.git $DEVSTACK" echo "Copy configuration" # copy localrc settings (source: devstack/samples/localrc) echo "copy config from $BASHPATH/config/localrc to $DEVSTACK/localrc" cp "$BASHPATH"/config/localrc "$DEVSTACK"/localrc chown "$OS_USER":"$OS_USER" "$DEVSTACK"/localrc fi # start devstack echo "Start Devstack" su "$OS_USER" -c "cd $DEVSTACK && ./stack.sh"

commit_message:
Make user to nonlocal_user a 1:1 relationship

The table relationship between 'user' and 'nonlocal_user' should be
1 to 1, which is consistent with 'user' to 'local_user'. However, it's
mistakenly 1 to many. In fact, the backend code treats 'user' to
'nonlocal_user' as 1:1 and wouldn't allow duplicates, so this will have
zero impact on existing deployments. This patch fixes this by making the
user_id column unique.

Closes-Bug: #1649412
Partially-Implements: bp support-federated-attr
Change-Id: Ib371df18f3fb2c67e5421cf0bf4551183902cf00

commit_message:
bump upper constraints of libvirt-python to 2.1.0

centos7 updated libvirt and libvirt-devel package to version
2.0.0-10.el7_3.2 and this will make installation of libvirt-python
below version number 2.0.0 fail, so bump the upper constrains of
libvirt-python to install newer version.

closes-bug: 1636567

Change-Id: Ia8d48e43cdbc491ac03b7273d6aaa1625dbeb07a

commit_message:
Modify variable's usage in Log Messages

String interpolation should be delayed to be handled by the logging code,
rather than being done at the point of the logging call.
Ref:http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/guidelines.html#log-translation
For example:
LOG.info(_LI('some message: variable=%s') % variable)
LOG.info(_LI('some message: variable=%s'), variable)

Change-Id: Ib3d5c1bae1a4fdb2c6b0d83591e5ae29a27ec1fb

commit_message:
Adds distribution ID option to diskimage-create.sh

This patch adds a distribution ID option to the diskimage-create.sh
script used to create amphora images.  This will allow octavia
to control the timing of the transition to a new default release.
For newton it will default to "trusty".

This also pins the tripleo-image-elements to stable/newton.

Change-Id: I435cf9f4723fc9e68f8cb8987c8316b09e6876b6
Closes-Bug: 1642756
(cherry picked from commit 2db260c95a326404d4ea4a33efe6c4151f29fb59)

commit_message:
Pinning tripleo-image-elements to a mitaka commit

Tripleo-image-elements did not create a stable/mitaka branch and
master is currently broken with stable/mitaka code.  This patch
pins our use of tripleo-image-elements to the last commit in the
mitaka timeframe.  It allows a successful stable/mitaka devstack
of octavia.

Change-Id: Icf045edb148e6f0e64e63e3c274be43681bf3980

commit_message:
Fix plan delete

As part of the overcloud delete implementation, we refactored the plan
delete to be a shared function. Unforunately the wrong inputs were being
passed to the workflow so it would return an Invalid input error. This
change fixes the input so that the container is properly passed to the
workflow as an input.

Change-Id: I33032c9e6f4a8cf002e65ebab60752c44fb5fdb2
Closes-Bug: #1647747

commit_message:
Fix mariadb-libs issue for non p-o-i jobs

CentOS 7.3 ships a new version of mariadb-libs which
conflicts with the version in RDO.

For p-o-i scenarios jobs this has been fixed in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/403164/ but rspec
jobs which use openstack_integration::repos but not
run_tests.sh are still failing.

This should be reverted once a new non-conflicting package
is released by RDO.

Change-Id: Ib43ac25f96994c9373fd1e848f229ec713dd54b7
(cherry picked from commit 3b6bc5bb3ee63cf23ae56cfbf7c102799f2480b4)

commit_message:
Cleanup after fixing mitaka gate

Some workarounds were implemented in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/411416 to
unblock mitaka gate.

This change removes all those workarounds
which are not longer required as have been implemented
properly in:

https://review.openstack.org/411437
https://review.openstack.org/410749
https://review.openstack.org/411546
https://review.openstack.org/410823

I prefer to send this instead of a revert because we
must keep the "yum update" in run_tests.sh.

commit_message:
Deprecate compute options

Marked following config options as deprecated:
1. multi_instance_display_name_template
2. null_kernel

API behaviour should not be changed through these flags and these
value should be hard coded.

Blueprint centralize-config-options-ocata

Change-Id: I613be6a42b3f2163fc7aa10f40b1a087306f89dd

commit_message:
Add support of endpoint_type and region_name to clients manila uses

Since change [1] it is impossible to set endpoint_type and region_name
for nova, cinder and neutron clients that are used by manila in some
cases.
So, to fix it, add additional options called 'endpoint_type' and
'region_name' for each of config groups related to these clients.
These options can be defined in appropriate config group as following:

[nova]
endpoint_type = publicURL
region_name = SomeRegionName

[cinder]
endpoint_type = internalURL
region_name = SomeRegionName

[neutron]
endpoint_type = adminURL
region_name = SomeRegionName

Also, combined it with small commit [2] this change depends on.

[1] Ic211a11308a3295409467efd88bff413482ee58d
[2] I84d67546e541b29f127057e6c7da990db71f6955

Change-Id: I6be0e77bbc0e4b1e9905eba7a7b48ff540e9e377
Closes-Bug: #1633454
(cherry picked from commit 11b38f3188686368412cdbb22ef55570720e3002)
(cherry picked from commit 1248814e22ee57b233d79a4c8246088836fd0e7a)

Fix typos

1. What is the problem?
There were some typos in this module, which should be modified.

2. What is the solution to the problem?

3. What the features need to be implemented to the Tricircle to
realize the solution?
No new features

commit_message:
Non-WAN port filter issue in Kaminario iSCSI driver

To attach Kaminario iSCSI volume to a nova instance, we search
K2 API "system/net_ips" with filter wan_port="". But it is not able to
filter non-WAN ports.

Change-Id: If58cf5b9bdc13f72313aba68e54af6ec2f907703
Closes-Bug: #1646692
Co-Authored-By: Lakshman<Lakshmi.Narayana.ctr@kaminario.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ido Benda<Ido.Benda@kaminario.com>

commit_message:
[ZFSonLinux] Stop inheriting options creating share from snapshot

Because, it leads to inheritance of access rules too. That is a bug.
All other expected options are generated on-fly already.

Change-Id: Ibe744c9fd001156a8184aa8f955c424cebfb8664
Closes-Bug: #1645746

commit_message:
Fix some python3 string issues in amphora agent

The amphora agent has some code that is not handling python3 strings
properly.
This patch resolves that issue.

Change-Id: Ib1af8287bf126aa2aa4626b5ac067bbe20eaa5d2

commit_message:
Cleanup Newton Release Notes

Do not show versions 13.0.0 in the Newton release notes - see
http://docs.openstack.org/releasenotes/nova/newton.html

This adds the earliest-version directive to only show the Newton release
which was 14.0.0.

Also, do not generate an index file, it is empty, see:
http://docs.openstack.org/releasenotes/nova/genindex.html

Change-Id: Id24268bf4ecef1427ea727654bb07c7e8a848d59

commit_message:
Add schedule_and_build_instances conductor method

This patch is part of refactoring to move instance saving to the
conductor. It only creates new conductor manager method to schedule and
build instance.

The new method does quite the same thing as build_instances but has some
differences:
- build_requests and request_spec are used instead of
  instances param
- it's cell aware i.e. it creates instance and related
  objects in the appropriate cell
- in the case of failure method creates instance in cell0

Co-Authored-By: Dan Smith <dansmith@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I19d6d765894785b214458b32fe612b4ef78a270d
Implements: bp cells-scheduling-interaction

deleted_lines: self.compute_task_api.build_instances(context, instances=instances, image=boot_meta, filter_properties=filter_properties, admin_password=admin_password, injected_files=injected_files, requested_networks=requested_networks, security_groups=security_groups, block_device_mapping=block_device_mapping, legacy_bdm=False)

subject: Make get_partitions() work for partitioned disks
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-11-21 12:36:44.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/tempest/commit/9a366813da271593b5344a3b99d9ffb50241938f', 'message': "Make get_partitions() work for partitioned disks

In general case, attached disks could be partitioned,
and this leads to multiple records in /proc/partitions,
for my laptop which is:
evgeny@eantyshev2:~$ cat /proc/partitions
major minor  #blocks  name

   8        0  125034840 sda
   8        1     524288 sda1
   8        2     249856 sda2
   8        3  124259328 sda3
   8       16  976762584 sdb
  11        0    1048575 sr0
 252        0 1084366848 dm-0
 252        1   16650240 dm-1

QEMU adds block devices as unpartitioned disks, so that
we have 1 disk <-> 1 partition match. But this is just
an implementation specific coincidence.
Because the attached disk can have GPT table
and a primary partition covering available disk space, and in this
case it would mean 2 extra devices.

Namely, to run Tempest on Virtuozzo containers, we should allow for
partitioned disks attached.

CT-f9e98104 /# cat /proc/partitions
major minor  #blocks  name

 182   686608    2097152 ploop42913
 182   686609    2095104 ploop42913p1
 182   506688    1048576 ploop31668
 182   506689    1046528 ploop31668p1

Here we see 2 devices for each disk: root disk block device ploop31668,
and partition block device ploop31668p1. We only want to see
root device for each disk, not the partition ones, or
some testcases don't work
(test_verify_created_server_ephemeral_disk naturally expects
device appearance of 1 extra device).

Change-Id: Icd0043b661c41a51acf62cc07cb80c2e9bae56d4

commit_message:
Make get_partitions() work for partitioned disks

In general case, attached disks could be partitioned,
and this leads to multiple records in /proc/partitions,
for my laptop which is:
evgeny@eantyshev2:~$ cat /proc/partitions
major minor  #blocks  name

   8        0  125034840 sda
   8        1     524288 sda1
   8        2     249856 sda2
   8        3  124259328 sda3
   8       16  976762584 sdb
  11        0    1048575 sr0
 252        0 1084366848 dm-0
 252        1   16650240 dm-1

QEMU adds block devices as unpartitioned disks, so that
we have 1 disk <-> 1 partition match. But this is just
an implementation specific coincidence.
Because the attached disk can have GPT table
and a primary partition covering available disk space, and in this
case it would mean 2 extra devices.

Namely, to run Tempest on Virtuozzo containers, we should allow for
partitioned disks attached.

CT-f9e98104 /# cat /proc/partitions
major minor  #blocks  name

 182   686608    2097152 ploop42913
 182   686609    2095104 ploop42913p1
 182   506688    1048576 ploop31668
 182   506689    1046528 ploop31668p1

Here we see 2 devices for each disk: root disk block device ploop31668,
and partition block device ploop31668p1. We only want to see
root device for each disk, not the partition ones, or
some testcases don't work
(test_verify_created_server_ephemeral_disk naturally expects
device appearance of 1 extra device).

Change-Id: Icd0043b661c41a51acf62cc07cb80c2e9bae56d4

commit_message:
Fetch images in a standalone role

This functionality is useful in non-libvirt environments, so separate it
and include it with the new Ansible 2.2 include_role method.

Change-Id: I2ed5dd8115cce012a007b7d791777b052034a17a

commit_message:
Remove iBoot, WoL and AMT drivers

This patch removes the mentioned drivers from ironic code tree.

Per our third-party drivers policy they are unsupported,
and there is no existing plan to have third-party CI for them.

Nevertheless, if anybody still needs them, they are available in
ironic-staging-drivers repo.

Change-Id: I1219892bbc1b814d80b62c8ec89b90819071870f
Related-Bug: #1640533

task.driver.vendor.continue_deploy(task) mock_ensure.assert_called_with( task.driver.management, task.node, boot_devices.PXE) mock_pxe_vendorpassthru.assert_called_once_with( task.driver.vendor, task) commit_message:
Create mechanism for enabling placement-client on subnodes

When doing multinode devstack we need a way to specify that we've
enabled for the placement service. We use a pseudo service of
placement-client for this.

Change-Id: I04a655fbc58913b3d607400a7f677be299499142
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/devstack refs/changes/10/411510/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD

We configure the placement service for nova # if placement-api or placement-client is active, and n-cpu on the # same box. if is_service_enabled placement placement-client; then if is_service_enabled n-cpu; then configure_placement_nova_compute fi fi

commit_message:
Fix flavor_client create_flavor interface

In flavor_clients compute service client, create_flavor
method does not allow to pass 0/none/false etc for
'OS-FLV-EXT-DATA:ephemeral' and 'os-flavor-access:is_public'.

https://github.com/openstack/tempest/blob/d12c233343aa490a23b9ffd3a58c5df6ff2bf9da/tempest/lib/services/compute/flavors_client.py#L70-L72

Code should check existence if those in kwargs instead of
their value and then populate the request body arg.

Change-Id: I0fda1aa2d126e10c986bfe445637d61e5b60de2d
Closes-Bug: #1650418

commit_message:
Fix LOG marker to follow the Python 3 guideline

"logging.warn" which is functionally identical to "logging.warning",
is deprecated in Python 3 as guideline [1].
we'd better use "logging.warning" instead.

[1]https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning

Change-Id: I3567e04b3d2c358a3e5b520b8c21598e2f0be70d

commit_message:
Fix mariadb-libs issue for non p-o-i jobs

CentOS 7.3 ships a new version of mariadb-libs which
conflicts with the version in RDO.

For p-o-i scenarios jobs this has been fixed in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/403164/ but rspec
jobs which use openstack_integration::repos but not
run_tests.sh are still failing.

This should be reverted once a new non-conflicting package
is released by RDO.

Change-Id: Ib43ac25f96994c9373fd1e848f229ec713dd54b7

commit_message:
Deprecate eventlet parameters

Eventlet parameters are deprecated, have no effect and will be
removed in a future release. Stop using public_port, admin_port,
public_bind_host and admin_bind_host but rather keystone::wsgi::apache
parameters.

Change-Id: Ie6225f91c4bb8caacb5108133fc0f1ba4e247e2b

configure_for_func_testing: don't install rabbitmq

commit_message:
Bump sphinx to 1.5.1 to avoid doc compilation failure

There is conflict between recent docutils and old sphinx which
lead to build error for external images or SVG images
(see https://sourceforge.net/p/docutils/bugs/301/)
The fix is included into Sphinx 1.5.1

Change-Id: Iecddc67fe19279326827b5b76fb084b4e316c78d

commit_message:
tripleo: allow to re-trigger ovb jobs only

Doing recheck takes a lot of time and resources, sometimes just to check
if OVB jobs pass (while other jobs in check pipeline already work).

Having 'ovb-recheck' would allow TripleO developers to only run OVB jobs
at wish. It would save time and resources.

Change-Id: I364288adb708bca5e12d12b2c918242c75b31b76

commit_message:
[proxy-api] microversion 2.39 deprecates image-metadata proxy API

Almost all proxy APIs were deprecated in microversion 2.36.
But the sub-resource image-metadata of image was forgotten to deprecate.
This patch deprecates the image-metdata API from 2.39.

Image commands were already deprecated since 2.36 in
I450917f7fcbfe0a3ea7921c82af9863e80cb40a1

Implements blueprint deprecate-image-meta-proxy-api

Change-Id: Idd4cd1d1fec13f9e5f89dc419b57e094c9ad4b3b

commit_message:
Fix issue of adding router interface from dashboard with specified IP

When adding a router-interface from dashboard with subnet and a
specified IP, the port in neutron DB contains security_groups default.
The networking-ovn adds router-interface IP to "Address_Set" of
Northbound-DB.
Actually, the router port need no security groups, this issue affects
lrouter's forwarding.
This patch fixes this bug. If security groups are present in a trusted
port we ignore them.

Change-Id: Ie872510416f50fcee7ec6d3760006b095621bff9
Closes-Bug: #1647949
Signed-off-by: Dong Jun <dongj@dtdream.com>

commit_message:
Fix zuul layout order for tripleo scenarios

Zuul layout order wasn't correct for tripleo scenarios, the jobs were
still running on stable/hammer branch because the rule was overriden by
the rule moved in this patch.

Moving this 'general' rule before specific rules makes the layout safer
so we first define the general rule and then the specific rules for the rest.

Change-Id: I77c342d57302c0e6a0d550e3a211b06190fd4666

commit_message:
Introduce generic hardware types

This change adds ironic.drivers.generic.GenericHardware which contains
useful defaults. Other hardware types are recommended to derive from it.

Add reasonable vendor-independent defaults to enabled_{deploy,raid,boot}_interfaces
configuration options. Add an entry point for "inspector" inspect implementation.

Also adding ironic.drivers.generic.ManualManagementHardware. This hardware
type is mostly introduced to make unit testing of GenericHardware possible.
However, it also has a potential use case: hardware not covered by
an existing driver or when an existing driver misbehaves. I personally
know people using fake_pxe currently in production for such use cases.

Change-Id: I328191524eb71c2ef51fec02c9cb28087dcf663b
Partial-Bug: #1524745

You may obtain # a copy of the License at # # http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 # # Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software # distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT # WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. See the # License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations # under the License. """ Generic hardware types. """ from ironic.drivers import hardware_types from ironic.drivers.modules import agent from ironic.drivers.modules import inspector from ironic.drivers.modules import iscsi_deploy from ironic.drivers.modules.network import flat as flat_net from ironic.drivers.modules.network import neutron from ironic.drivers.modules.network import noop as noop_net from ironic.drivers.modules import noop from ironic.drivers.modules import pxe class GenericHardware(hardware_types.AbstractHardwareType): """Abstract base class representing generic hardware. This class provides reasonable defaults for boot, deploy and inspect interfaces. """ @property def supported_boot_interfaces(self): """List of supported boot interfaces.""" return [pxe.PXEBoot] @property def supported_deploy_interfaces(self): """List of supported deploy interfaces.""" return [iscsi_deploy.ISCSIDeploy, agent.AgentDeploy] @property def supported_inspect_interfaces(self): """List of supported inspect interfaces.""" return [noop.NoInspect, inspector.Inspector] @property def supported_network_interfaces(self): """List of supported network interfaces.""" return [flat_net.FlatNetwork, neutron.NeutronNetwork, noop_net.NoopNetwork]

commit_message:
Use oslo-config-generator for sample config

The old generate_sample.sh is broken already as it refers to
non-existing openstack/common path.

Let's use oslo-config-generator as many other OpenStack projects do.

Also, where applicable, option descriptions are updated with the
corresponding kernel parameters to set those options durig pxe boot.

Change-Id: Id4a0df30ea573d52f3b359f357fe8f4a29751939

commit_message:
Replace logging with oslo_log.

The oslo.log (logging) configuration library provides standardized
configuration for all openstack projects. It also provides custom
formatters, handlers and support for context specific logging (like
resource id's etc).

Change-Id: I1f1adb198c34da711cd7e8e370d39a9e3cea6f50

commit_message:
Avoid opening parents when fetching VHD info

This change ensures that when a VHD is queried, the parent images
are not opened by default.

'get_vhd_info' now accepts the 'open_parents' argument, which can be
useful for validating a VHD chain.

Closes-Bug: #1648555

Change-Id: Ie6b4febb4357419e6bb6395b4abb0ab10006a4f0
(cherry picked from commit 6259f2c4190b0953ec181ef06c302f4b6d75e11b)

commit_message:
Remove v3 stub controller

This patch removes the stub controller for v3 that was introduced
in Mitaka when Glare became a standalone service.  As the v3 API
was always EXPERIMENTAL, this removal does not require a deprecation
period.  (Also, anyone interested in artifacts is using Glare, not
the v3 API.)

Change-Id: Ie16ba13c5970596eebf7b757c0712358c80f376e
Closes-bug: #1650108
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/glance refs/changes/92/411092/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
deleted_lines: # Copyright (c) 2015 Mirantis, Inc. # # Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License"); you may # not use this file except in compliance with the License. You may obtain # a copy of the License at # # http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 # # Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software # distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT # WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. See the # License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations # under the License. from oslo_log import log as logging from oslo_log import versionutils from glance.common import wsgi from glance.i18n import _LW LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__) """v3 controller stub Since Glance Artifact Service was released in Liberty as experimental Glance v3 API, its router was referenced in paste configuration as glance.api.v3.router In Mitaka the Artifacts Service was moved into a standalone process and its router was renamed to glance.api.artifacts.router. However, in existing deployments the glance-api-paste.ini may still reference the glance.api.v3.router. To not break these deployments this stub is included to redirect the v3 request to glare service (if it is present) or return a 410 otherwise. This stub controller should be removed in future releases. """ class API(wsgi.Router): def __init__(self, mapper): versionutils.report_deprecated_feature( LOG, _LW('/v3 controller is deprecated and will be removed from ' 'glance-api soon. Remove the reference to it from ' 'glance-api-paste.ini configuration file and use Glance ' 'Artifact Service API instead')) redirector = self._get_redirector() mapper.connect(None, "/artifacts", controller=redirector, action='redirect') mapper.connect(None, "/artifacts/{path:.*}", controller=redirector, action='redirect') super(API, self).__init__(mapper) def _get_redirector(self): return wsgi.Resource(RedirectController(), serializer=RedirectResponseSerializer()) class RedirectController(object): def redirect(self, req, path=None): try: glare_endpoint = next((s['endpoints'] for s in req.context.service_catalog if s['type'] == 'artifact'))[0]['publicURL'] if path: path = '/' + path return '{0}/v0.1/artifacts{1}'.format(glare_endpoint, path or "") except StopIteration: return None class RedirectResponseSerializer(wsgi.JSONResponseSerializer): def default(self, response, res): if res: response.location = res response.status_int = 301 else: response.status_int = 410

Add a trunk rally test

This adds a basic rally scenario to create a trunk
with a bunch of subports so we can keep an eye on the
performance of the trunk API.

commit_message:
pin ansible-lint at v3.4.7 until we resolve issues with 3.4.8

The root cause for failures when running with 3.4.8 has not yet been
found.  Use v3.4.7 until we've determined the root cause.

Error in 3.4.8 http://paste.openstack.org/show/592635/

Change-Id: Ib5652dc3967b2571444345514841d1143bf05b33

commit_message:
Add drac_address to ipmi_address_fields

Since Ia23e8582a398dca9ca11762ee6fe1789fdba9777 ironic's DRAC drivers
deprecated 'drac_host' driver_info field in favor of 'drac_address'.

This patch adds 'drac_address' to default value for 'ipmi_address_fields'
config option so that inspector can support both nodes with old and new
driver_info field.

Change-Id: I90559d7a99462cd0de2a0c8ce047015955b8cfda
Related-Bug: #1644210

commit_message:
Refactor ml2_db to pass context

We have a number of functions that expect to get session as one of
the arguments. Passing session is not correct and this prevents
the usage of new enginefacade which expect context to be passed
and session will be injected in current context.

NeutronLibImpact

Change-Id: If600033de801e1a3759919b272ac52f0850bf49c

commit_message:
Speed up graph && node processing

- in case of big number of node (more then 200) and tasks
(more then 20000), progress calculation can slow down
- remove status magent call from puppet run (decrease number
  of magent calls from 2 to 1 in case of positive scenario)

Change-Id: I70675a6bbd391d0112c594626bdb0ce7bb9e3e1e

Change-Id: I1f38815e188b4d0cd72b15d66319194fcfce1e0a

commit_message:
Use patch-port:vlan i.o. linux interface as linuxif

Providing the linuxinterface (qvoxxxx) as 'linuxif' to bagpipe-bgp
is not as harmless as it should be, because this is the key used
to determine when the last plug on an interface is done.

This patch provides the patch-port:vlan tuple instead, which should
allow bagpipe-bgp current code to properly identify the unplug of the
last VM on a Network on a given compute node.

Change-Id: I1f38815e188b4d0cd72b15d66319194fcfce1e0a
Closes-Bug: 1644151
(cherry picked from commit e715f1531d1bd2c776a8d1cf02a80ffb80ebb25e)

commit_message:
Speed up graph && node processing

- in case of big number of node (more then 200) and tasks
(more then 20000), progress calculation can slow down
- remove status magent call from puppet run (decrease number
  of magent calls from 2 to 1 in case of positive scenario)

Change-Id: I70675a6bbd391d0112c594626bdb0ce7bb9e3e1e

commit_message:
Fix pylint too-many-return-statements errors

This patch fixes the errors noted by pylint whereby too many
return statements are within a single method/function.

The following errors were resolved:
************* Module bandit.core.context
R:196, 4: Too many return statements (10/6) (too-many-return-statements)

Change-Id: I1caf37effb94c4d8123f99d3bb485e1fa0af8272

commit_message:
[WIP] Move mitaka to ceph jewel instead of hammer

Ceph hammer is EOL and have some conflicts with CentOS 7.3.
This patch moves p-o-i to jewel for stable/mitaka branch.

Change-Id: I7401399dc8cb1979069bde594e9495567391a77f
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/puppet-openstack-integration refs/changes/92/409892/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: # We use jewel for all active releases, including mitaka # so we must use puppet-ceph master branch. PUPPET_CEPH_ZUUL_BRANCH="master"
deleted_lines: # Workaround for puppet-ceph, where we need to checkout # OpenStack modules from stable/mitaka when working on stable/hammer. # Ceph Hammer works with Mitaka and before. # Ceph Jewel works with Newton and beyond. if [ "$ZUUL_BRANCH" == "stable/hammer" ] || [ "$ZUUL_BRANCH" == "stable/mitaka" ]; then PUPPET_CEPH_ZUUL_BRANCH='stable/hammer' ZUUL_BRANCH='stable/mitaka' else PUPPET_CEPH_ZUUL_BRANCH=$ZUUL_BRANCH ZUUL_BRANCH=$ZUUL_BRANCH fi

commit_message:
Provide a way to install docker-py from packaging in bootstrap

The version of docker-py in CentOS, Debian and Ubuntu all satisfy
the minimum requirement >=1.6.0, let's provide a toggle to install
it from packaging instead of pip.

Change-Id: I3f70f1312ef4d0f304788aca8655b7477e1728b3

commit_message:
Turn off tempest's multitenant network tests

This disables the multitenant networking tests that come from tempest's
tree, but not the ones in ironic's tempest plugin.

commit_message:
Correct murano-dashboard reraising of exception

When an exception was caught and rethrown, it should call 'raise'
without any arguments because it shows the place where an exception
occured initially instead of place where the exception re-raised.

Change-Id: I8f82ffebd2feba1b45979e7bcebdc32c66952485
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/murano-dashboard refs/changes/92/408392/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: except Exception: raise
deleted_lines: except Exception as e: raise e

commit_message:
Move CONF.service_available.ironic to our plugin

This is unwanted in tempest's plugin, bring it here instead.

Also add skip checks for our tests to skip the tests if ironic is not
enabled. This allows the plugin to be installed in a tempest
environment, without breaking if ironic isn't present.

Last, drop 'baremetal' from the test.services decorators used, as it is
no longer in tempest's service list, and we use the skip check mentioned
above instead.

Change-Id: I0b7e32dfad2ed63f9dd4d7cad130da39bc869a8a
Depends-On: Idede322190d57491d4f7e18090aa8c29b5b87353
(cherry picked from commit 8ad0a424b3e3963b9fdda0e1b64d8a065ef978d2)

added_lines: if not CONF.service_available.ironic: raise cls.skipException('Ironic is not enabled.')

commit_message:
Upgrade libraries, add highlight for JSON data

Upgrade libraries:
    - Angular      1.2.10  -> 1.6.0
    - Angular UI   0.11.0  -> 2.3.1
    - Bootstrap    3.2.0   -> 3.3.7

Remove old-style Bootstrap 2 CSS
Move template from JS concatenate to template section
Change naming convention to camelCase

Angular style [1][2][3]:
    - `vm syntax`
    - `controller as` syntax
    - $inject property annotation [4]
    - IIFE for JS section instead of global variable all the time

Add highlight.js for JSON in metadata section (when open modal)
Add close button for modal
Add toggle wrap text button for modal

Preview output change:
    - Current: https://embed.plnkr.co/tfL1RHLJBvHR5om9ZoII/?show=preview
    - New: https://embed.plnkr.co/9s3uUy6v4OUpuYSrludz/?show=preview
    - Compare: https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/16864276/compare_trace.png

[1] https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md
[2] https://github.com/toddmotto/angular-styleguide

commit_message:
Move openvswitch db file into docker volume

openvswitch db file is created in /etc/openvswitch/conf.db. It will be
lost during upgrade openvswitch_db container.

This patch moves the db file into /var/lib/openvswitch folder, which
located in docker volume.

Change-Id: I73604fddacd21655590b9e66ee2805014795b9f1
Closes-Bug: #1649290
(cherry picked from commit f62b16f8a447b7c90da3844720a200fb4d3ef5d5)

commit_message:
Load DATABASE_USER from stackrc

mariadb does not use DATABASE_USER = 'root' by default.
New versions of MySQL flavor MariaDB do not allow remote access for
'root' user by default.
This patch enables non-root users by loading DATABASE_USER variable
from stackrc (which is loaded by MYSQL_USER in localrc). It keeps 'root'
user as default for MySQL.

Change-Id: I15f5f7ca1fe91d97b3f5bf268982b133513e5e3c
(cherry picked from commit 6d3e6cfbfb9ce7d218381a0f001ca413aef6f55d)

added_lines: local database_user=$( set +o xtrace && source $dir/stackrc && echo ${DATABASE_USER:-root}) mysqldump -u$database_user -p$mysql_pass $db >$SAVE_DIR/$db.sql.$release

commit_message:
replace assertTrue with assertIs.

[H203] 'assertTrue' should also be avoided when 
more specific methods are available (assertIs instead of 
assertTrue), because they provide a better error message 
in case of failure.

commit_message:
Remove priority for non-delorean RDO repos

RDO doesn't set priority in repository configuration via
rdo-release or centos openstack releases rpms.

This is currently being a problem as dependencies for qemu-kvm-ev-2.6.0
must be resolved from base and RDO ships same packages with lower VR
for historical reasons.

Depends-On: Ic95755a927eef0580433cd5c8eca1c4c7cad2f69
Change-Id: Ifb0ec9ca8a98a15984145972e99915e7eb23eb99
(cherry picked from commit f1ab3bba85920318094ac5261005e938ad7ef2e5)

commit_message:
[WIP] Enable adoption of subnets into a subnet pool

This patch enables the adoption of existing subnets into a
subnetpool. Adoption of a subnet is done by passing the ID
of the hosting network and the address family (ip_version)
which causes all subnets in the specified address family
on the given network to be adopted by the subnet pool. This
continues to work within the constraints on subnet pool
membership of subnets on the same network. This also ensures
prefix uniqueness across an address scope before comitting the
adoption of subnets.

This is a continuation of the previous commit:
    https://review.openstack.org/#/c/348080/

Co-Authored-By: Ryan Tidwell <ryan.tidwell@hpe.com>
Change-Id: Icb7d690aa06cc7f4f6a69a234914b820728ace07
Partially-Implements: blueprint subnet-onboard

commit_message:
Create symlink which is required for master node plugin tasks

Place where plugins are linked depends on configuration (of Nailgun,
MCollective, Astute), hence must not be hardcoded in specs and
should be done by puppet manifests which own master node configuration
details.

Change-Id: I1e9db92f9fc8dc70403113d1d6f9062b689dd2ee
Related-bug: #1603987
Closes-bug: #1648882

commit_message:
Replace six.iteritems() with .items()

1.As mentioned in [1], we should avoid using
six.iteritems to achieve iterators. We can
use dict.items instead, as it will return
iterators in PY3 as well. And dict.items/keys
will more readable. 2.In py2, the performance
about list should be negligible, see the link [2].
[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3
[2] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

Change-Id: Ic6af69d5b4b36f3dd02aab0f9c446aa54970f388

This reverts commit 3e777cd8f4e7237151f71637a0ef8230692b96ae.

commit_message:
Add output validation for substitution mappings

1. Validate that the attributes of the substitution mappings node type can be
accessed in the service template by substituted node.
2.Validate that an attempt to access any attributes not belong to a specific
node type or substitution mappings results into an expected error.

This patch is related to bp: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/345492/

Co-Authored-By: Sahdev Zala <spzala@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I5f6cdcf7eb66f20ba9e524b73edd249d2c7b1e31

commit_message:
Add UI Tests for Filtering Apps by Tag/Description.

Also made the following changes:
  - Renamed test_check_search_option -> test_filter_by_name,
    because now that there are multiple search option tests,
    this test more precisely conveys what it is testing.
  - Added helper function wait_for_page_reload to base.py,
    because after a filter is conducted, a page refresh is
    performed; on slow machines, not waiting for page refresh
    throws error, because content hasn't loaded yet.

Change-Id: Ifecba6563877de7d28b3d3ab4e2b77774b993c7e
Partial-Bug: #1596196

commit_message:
Add UI Test for Abandon Environment from Detail View.

Also removed the helper function wait_element_is_viewable,
because it is redundant; it can be substituted for the following
function instead:
  - check_element_on_page
The removed was only being used by
test_delete_environment_from_detail_view, which has been updated
to use the aforementioned function instead.

Also added 3 new constants:
 - DetailDropdownBtn: the toggle button that needs to be clicked
   on in the env detail view to toggle dropdown menu
 - DetailDropdownMenu: the menu after clicking the former
 - ModalDialog: - the confirmation modal dialog itself

Change-Id: I7e326e697413c710781d8aa5daf92aa5fbebfbb2
Partial-Bug: #1596196

commit_message:
Accept multiple hosts when calling live migration

Live migration requests to a specific host can now fail because the host will
be validated by the scheduler. This may result in several round-trips to the
API before a valid host is found. It would be much more efficient to also
accept a list of hosts from which the scheduler can select.

Blueprint specify-multiple-live-migrate-hosts

Change-Id: I3f58a60334ded95127b9fdcb6098590a294f9e11
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/nova-specs refs/changes/40/276840/7 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: .. This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported License. http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/legalcode ================================================= Accept multiple hosts when calling live migration ================================================= https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/specify-multiple-live-migrate-hosts Live migration requests to a specific host can now fail because the host will be validated by the scheduler. This may result in several round-trips to the API before a valid host is found. It would be much more efficient to also accept a list of hosts, with Nova trying each one, in order, until one succeeds. Problem description =================== Now that the live migration API will validate the target host with the scheduler, it is possible that calls will fail, due to the specified target not passing the original request's specifications. In order to avoid multiple calls to the live_migration API, it would be more efficient to also accept a list of hostnames, and have Nova attempt to migrate to each, in order, until one succeeds. If all hosts fail, only then would a 400 Bad Request be returned. Use Cases --------- As a deployer trying to optimize resource usage in my cloud, I sometimes need to live migrate instances to different hosts. As there may be several acceptable hosts, I would like to pass that list of hosts to Nova instead of manually passing them one at a time until one succeeds. As an automated tool that is trying to optimize resource usage in a cloud, I would like to let Nova know of all the acceptable hosts for live migrating an instance, rather than having to implement the retry loop around this call and potentially making multiple round-trip API calls. Proposed change =============== In order to implement this change, the live migration code in nova/api/openstack/compute/migrate_server.py will need to be changed. Specifically,the `_migrate_live` method will be modified to determine if the value passed in the request body is a single hostname or comma-separated list of hostname. In the case of a single hostname, it will be converted to a one-element list. The method will then iterate over the list, and catch any of the exceptions that currently raise a BadRequest. If there are most hostnames to try, it will retry with the next hostname in the list, until either the call does not raise an error, or the list of hostnames is exhausted. In the latter situation, a BadRequest exception will be raised. Novaclient may also have to be modified to accept multiple arguments for the host, and turn that into a comma-separated list that is passed to the Nova API. Optionally, the current code could remain as is, and the user would have to type in the hosts as a comma-separated string to the `--host` argument. In either case, the documentation will have to be updated. Alternatives ------------ We could do nothing, and have the admin user or tool handle the retries themselves, at the cost of an API call per retry. We could also implement a new API that would accept an instance and a list of hostnames, and have that API return the list of those hosts which are valid migration targets. This option was discussed on IRC, and it was felt that it was too racy to be particularly useful, as the status of any host could change between getting the result and then calling live migrate with that host. There could also be thousands of acceptable hosts in a large cloud, and this would require pagination and multiple calls to get them all, further increasing the likelihood of stale information. Data model impact ----------------- None REST API impact --------------- The API would not change in format at all, but will add an interpretation of an existing parameter that will effectively change the overall API call. The existing documentation for the call for live migration would only have to be changed with respect to the `host` parameter. It would have to be updated to explain that acceptable values are either a single string representing the target host, or a comma-separated list of target hosts, in addition to being omitted. The proposed wording would be: "The host or hosts to which you wish to migrate the server. You may specify a single host, or a list of hosts, separated by commas. If you specify a list of hosts, they will be tried in order until either one succeeds, or all hosts fail. If you omit this parameter, the scheduler chooses a host." Neither the normal response codes nor the error response codes would change. Security impact --------------- None Notifications impact -------------------- None Other end user impact --------------------- As mentioned above, an admin using python-novaclient will now be able to specify multiple hosts when calling live-migration. The two possible ways of supporting this would be: a) require the hosts to be sent in a comma-delimited list; e.g: --host aa,bb,cc b) allow the host parameter to be specified multiple times; e.g.: --host aa --host bb --host cc In either case, the hosts will be sent to the Nova API as a comma-separated list. Performance Impact ------------------ There should be no impact on Nova's functioning, as not making this change would result in the same number of migration attempts in the case where multiple attempts are made before one succeeds. The performance gain will be in the process that is calling for the live migration, as it could potentially avoid several calls to the Nova API. Other deployer impact --------------------- None Developer impact ---------------- None Implementation ============== Assignee(s) ----------- Primary assignee: Ed Leafe <ed-leafe> Other contributors: None Work Items ---------- * Modify the _migrate_live method of nova/api/openstack/compute/migrate_server.py to parse the passed hosts into a list. * Add a retry loop to _migrate_live to catch the failures that would currently raise a BadRequest, and retry if there are more possible hosts to consider. * Add unit tests as described below in the 'Testing' section. Dependencies ============ * The `Check the destination host when migrating` blueprint (https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/check-destination-on-migrations) is the impetus for this change. Now that a specified host can be rejected by the scheduler, we should make the process more efficient by implementing this change. Testing ======= New tests will be added to nova/tests/unit/api/openstack/compute/test_migrate_server.py to test the following: * specifying multiple hosts, first succeeds * specifying multiple hosts, first fails * specifying multiple hosts, all fail Documentation Impact ==================== The documentation for live migration will have to be updated to explain the additional option of passing multiple hosts. References ========== There was an IRC discussion in #openstack-nova on 2016-02-03 in which different ideas were discussed, with the approach embodied in this spec being favored by all as the best compromise of different interests. The discussion begins at 20:40, and ends at 21:36; apologies for the wrapping, but the URL is too long: http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-nova/%23openstack-nova. 2016-02-03.log.html History =======

commit_message:
Glance Expand/Contract migrations with Alembic

This spec outlines the motivation and implementation details for porting
Glance database migrations from SQLAlchemy-based scripts to Alembic.

Change-Id: Ia8e72ce863ab8f2d1ba021f950dae1b8596cadfa
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/glance-specs refs/changes/78/374278/4 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: .. This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported License. http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/legalcode ======================================================= Change from SQLAlchemy to Alembic managed DB migrations ======================================================= https://blueprints.launchpad.net/glance/+spec/alembic-migrations This spec outlines the motivation and implementation details for porting Glance database migrations from SQLAlchemy-based scripts to Alembic. Problem description =================== Existing database migrations are implemented in Glance using SQLAlchemy- migrate scripts. This approach makes designing migrations for rolling upgrades ([1]_ & [2]_) extremely uncomfortable. The ``expand`` and ``contract`` migrations would have to be created in strict sequential order with all of the latter following all of the former. This places unnecessary restrictions on the order of migrations and becomes very error prone as multiple schema changes are introduced in a single cycle. Essentially, using SQLAlchemy-migrate constrains expand and contract migrations to be run atomically and does not easily facilitate separating them into phases as required during rolling upgrades. Proposed change =============== We are proposing to port the migration flows to be handled by Alembic [3]_. There are numerous benefits to this change. Alembic allows labeling the various migration scripts with designated branch names (i.e. ``expand`` and ``contract``), which makes it easier to group the two types of changes and run them separately. Additionally, Alembic supports automatic generation of migration scripts using SQLAlchemy's ORM. In the future, developers are encouraged to utilize this feature to minimize their interaction with the underlying DBMS and rely on the Python code to define the new schema. Alternatives ------------ The best aleternative available is to continue using SQLAlchemy-migrate scripts. The downsides of this appropach are outlined in the `Problem description`_ section above. Data model impact ----------------- None REST API impact --------------- None Security impact --------------- None Notifications impact -------------------- None Other end user impact --------------------- None Performance Impact ------------------ Performance of existing offline migration flows is not expected to be impacted in a signifficant way. Other deployer impact --------------------- There is no visible operator impact introduced with this change. The API of the glance-manage command-line utility remains backwards compatible. Even though new CLI commands are introduced in glance-manage, they will remain undocumented until rolling upgrades are implemented. See the `Documentation Impact`_ section below. Developer impact ---------------- Developers need to be aware of the this change and will need to create Alembic based migration scripts any time a database schema change is implemented. Implementation ============== Assignee(s) ----------- Primary assignee: hemanthm abashmak Work Items ---------- 1. Implement Alembic migration infrastructure and scripts for existing database migrations (up to Newton). 2. Introduce ``expand/contract`` migrations for new Ocata features [4]_. 3. Update the glance-manage utility to utilize Alembic for ``db_sync`` and related commands. Add ``db_expand`` and ``db_contract`` commands to prepare for rolling upgrades. Dependencies ============ * A new Python module will be added to Glance's requirements list: * *alembic* - version *0.8.7* or hihger Testing ======= Existing db migration tests (unit and functional) will be ported to utilize the updated glance-manage utility and test the integrity of migration scripts. Documentation Impact ==================== As part of the drive to enable the ``assert:supports-rolling-upgrade`` tag [5]_ this change will introduce and implement two new commands for the glance-manage utility: ``db_expand`` and ``db_contract``. Additionally, a placeholder stub is created for another command: ``db_data_migrate``. It is advised to wait until Glance is able to assert the rolling upgrade tag to add documentation for the new commands. References ========== .. [1] `Glance rolling upgrades <https://review.openstack.org/331489>`_ .. [2] `Database strategy for rolling upgrades <https://review.openstack.org/331740>`_ .. [3] `Alembic’s documentation <http://alembic.zzzcomputing.com/en/latest/>`_ .. [4] `Community images <https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/glance-specs/ specs/newton/approved/glance/community_visibility.html>`_ .. [5] `Supports rolling upgrade tag <https://governance.openstack.org/reference/ tags/assert_supports-rolling-upgrade.html>`_

commit_message:
Set cpu_mode to "none" when virt_type is qemu

The Nova code states that the default value for cpu_mode when using
qemu as virt_type should be host-model [1]. However, this is not
actually tested in the gate due to [2], and with QEMU 2.6.0 it is
known to cause issues [3], because there is a chance a new CPU
flag is used, but not emulated by QEMU TCG code.

Setting cpu_mode to "none" in this case as default would prevent us
from hitting issues when this code is most exercised, i.e. CI
environments.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/f419825c216bccd9f7023deec024099c5b65428d/nova/conf/libvirt.py#L442-L448
[2] https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/lib/nova_plugins/hypervisor-libvirt#L42
[3] https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1404627

Depends-On: I9fba274469ebbbe35b3aefb2476952ae1b3944fa
Change-Id: Ic95755a927eef0580433cd5c8eca1c4c7cad2f69
(cherry picked from commit 313eb84b2653821d02d68fc27c6f6c5b552c0b18)

commit_message:
Migrate neutron agent extensions to neutron-lib

Migrate neutron agent extensions to neutron-lib.  This includes both the
common abstract object as well as the l2 and l3-specific objects for
agent extensions.

This functionality is used by neutron, neutron-fwaas, networking-sfc,
and tap-as-a-service.

Please note that this does not migrate the l3_agent_extensions_api to
neutron-lib.  This is because that specifically has a long dependency
chain that ends up requiring agent/[linux,windows]/utils.py, which
should be migrated separately.

Change-Id: I7255a5ae6b706c09acecc0dea5dbd2febae0c282
Needed-By: I6d2cff03207924c7492c6136d4b21a9817769c67
Needed-By: If9235c1cf39b8ad2ef049e8154b82736e1f1d763
Needed-By: Ie8f0e70b11435d627f73e3fed45f946e863e90bc
Needed-By: Ia5962acfd737b4b350b94591802928a5a4dc53fb

You may obtain # a copy of the License at # # http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 # # Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software # distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT # WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. See the # License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations # under the License. from oslo_config import cfg from oslo_log import log import stevedore from neutron._i18n import _, _LI LOG = log.getLogger(__name__) AGENT_EXT_MANAGER_OPTS = [ cfg.ListOpt('extensions', default=[], help=_('Extensions list to use')), ] def register_opts(conf): conf.register_opts(AGENT_EXT_MANAGER_OPTS, 'agent') class AgentExtensionsManager(stevedore.named.NamedExtensionManager): """Manage agent extensions.""" def __init__(self, conf, namespace): super(AgentExtensionsManager, self).__init__( namespace, conf.agent.extensions, invoke_on_load=True, name_order=True) LOG.info(_LI("Loaded agent extensions: %s"), self.names()) def initialize(self, connection, driver_type, agent_api=None): """Initialize enabled agent extensions. :param connection: RPC connection that can be reused by extensions to define their RPC endpoints :param driver_type: a string that defines the agent type to the extension. Can be used by the extension to choose the right backend implementation. :param agent_api: an AgentAPI instance that provides an API to interact with the agent that the manager is running in. """ # Initialize each agent extension in the list. for extension in self: LOG.info(_LI("Initializing agent extension '%s'"), extension.name) # If the agent has provided an agent_api object, this object will # be passed to all interested extensions. This object must be # consumed by each such extension before the extension's # intialize() method is called, as the initilization step # relies on the agent_api already being available. extension.obj.consume_api(agent_api) extension.obj.initialize(connection, driver_type)

Pin to an older version until the issue can be resolved.
This patch should be reverted after the dependency problem is solved

commit_message:
Add support for manage/unmanage snapshots in HNAS driver

Adding support for manage/unmanage snapshots in Hitachi HNAS
driver. In order to manage a snapshot, the admin should provide the
snapshot size in "--driver-options" parameter.

Also, updating tempest tests for manage/unmanage snapshots to include
the required driver option.

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint hnas-manage-unmanage-snapshot-support

that version differs from the one expected: "CHECK constraint failed"
is expected, but "(sqlite3.IntegrityError) constraint failed" is
